Thank you &quot;Learned from the Pain&quot; I developed this idea while doing a research paper on Disabilities. I soon recognized that Vietnam Veterans have made a HUGE difference in many many lives by making a positive out of their negative situations.  I began to wonder just how many positive differences have been made as an individual and as a collective group. Suffering is a part of life..Suffering comes in many disguises...many we will never reason or understand...WAR is one of them...HOWEVER, a common thread in all suffering is a choice of attitude...lessons, differences and positive change of events from suffering is an amazing choice of human achievement in suffering. To entertain suffering through withdrawal and years of remorse <br>
makes even less sense then the orginal form of suffering itself...MTF-you can make good of the &quot;Folly&quot; of those &quot;young figthing men&quot; by understanding that many many people have been positively affected by the lessons learned from Vietnam and other forms of suffering.  It is your choice...
